OL,5, The number of Welsh speakers has fallen
OL,6, in the past decade, with fewer children
OL,7, speaking the language.                 
OL,9,FIn 2021, an estimated 538,000 people in
OL,10,FWales aged three years and over (17.8% 
OL,11,Fof the population) reported being able 
OL,12,Fto speak Welsh, data from the Office   
OL,13,Ffor National Statistics said.          
OL,15,FThat is a decrease since 2011 when     
OL,16,F562,000 or 19% spoke the language.     
OL,18,FOne of the main factors contributing to
OL,19,Fthe overall decrease is fewer Welsh    
OL,20,Fspeakers aged three to 15 years old.   
